article.headline: USC 64, SMU 48
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- In her first double-double of the season,
Ebony Hoffman scored 18 points and 13 rebounds to push USC's Women
of Troy past SMU 64-48 in a non-conference game Wednesday.

Rometra Craig scored 15 points, while Meghan Gnekow added 14
points for the Women of Troy.

USC led at halftime 32-19, using a 13-6 run at the start of the
second half to increase the margin to 20 points.

The Mustangs responded with an 11-3 run, but Craig put away one
of two three-pointers with 7:04 left in the game, rallying USC to
the victory.
